{"parentUuid":"bbe13c3a-51a1-4406-84ff-4d442d4f0b6a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcvyvjNbHGMXWur7XyYYL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MLqcwd9wo9x9fgPCqvpUZc","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"echo \"=== surface-delta.md ===\" && cat .pipeline/surface-delta.md 2>/dev/null || echo \"MISSING\"; echo \"=== ls .pipeline ===\"; ls -la .pipeline/ 2>/dev/null","description":"Read surface-delta hint and list pipeline dir"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":33305,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":553,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":33305},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":553,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":33305,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":33305,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcvyviUWoqRwkKYcfG4VK","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"84b40a6a-44ee-4e93-8a3c-0ca086df026e","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:30:10.168Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"84b40a6a-44ee-4e93-8a3c-0ca086df026e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c93d3662-5462-4799-b6d7-cd0b2d4e2c75","agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MLqcwd9wo9x9fgPCqvpUZc","type":"tool_result","content":"=== surface-delta.md ===\n# Attack-surface delta — GET /v1/usage/daily (per-metric daily usage summary)\n\nBest-effort hint for the security agent's diff reconciliation. The diff\n(`git diff HEAD --name-only` + `git ls-files --others --exclude-standard`) is\nthe source of truth; this file is advisory.\n\n## New entry points\n\n- **`GET /v1/usage/daily?date=YYYY-MM-DD`** — new HTTP route,\n  `src/api/routes/usage_daily.py:31` (`get_usage_daily_endpoint`), mounted via\n  `app.include_router(usage_daily_router)` in `src/main.py:90`. Customer-scoped\n  (any authenticated API key; no admin gate) — reads only the caller's own\n  tenant data, derived solely from the authenticated principal\n  (`principal.api_key_id`); the endpoint accepts no `customer_id`/`api_key_id`\n  input. Behind the same middleware edge stack as every other route (Tier-1 IP\n  throttle, body-size guard, security headers, CORS) plus a per-route Tier-2\n  per-`api_key_id` throttle (`src/api/routes/usage_daily.py:24`,\n  `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`).\n\n## New trust boundaries\n\n- None. No outbound third-party calls, no new subprocess/exec invocations, no\n  SSRF-capable fetches. The only boundaries this route crosses are the\n  existing API↔PostgreSQL boundary (governed by `scoped_transaction` + the\n  existing `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS policy) and the existing\n  API↔Redis boundary (Tier-2 throttle, reused unchanged).\n\n## New data flows / sinks\n\n- **New read query**: `aggregate_daily_event_counts`,\n  `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` (new function, appended after\n  `stream_usage_rollups`) — a `SELECT metric, SUM(event_count) ... GROUP BY\n  metric` over the existing `usage_rollup` table, scoped by `api_key_id =\n  :api_key_id` (bound parameter, from `principal.api_key_id`, never client\n  input) as the first predicate, plus the day-window bound parameters\n  (`:day_start`, `:day_end`) derived from the validated `date`. No new table,\n  no new column, no migration. All values are bound parameters — no string\n  interpolation of caller input into SQL text.\n- **No new stored data.** This is a pure read; nothing is written or\n  persisted by this change. No new field, no new data class, no new at-rest\n  control — `data-protection-conventions` is not triggered (the `usage_rollup`\n  rows it reads were already classified non-sensitive operational metering\n  data by the prior feature's interview; this change adds no new field).\n- **New logged event**: `usage.daily.read`,\n  `src/services/usage_daily_service.py` — `{userId: api_key_id, action:\n  \"read\", resource: \"usage_rollup\", date: <echoed date string>, metricCount:\n  <int>}`. No `customer_id` value, no metric *values*, no raw request/response\n  body logged — only the count of metrics returned. Routed through the\n  existing `get_logger()` facade (`src/logging/__init__.py`), which applies\n  the centralized redaction + control-character-stripping processors to every\n  log call regardless of call site.\n\n## New privilege / authz surface\n\n- **No new authenticated route class.** The route depends only on\n  `require_api_key` (existing facade, unchanged) — no new admin/scope gate is\n  introduced, and none is required (deliberately: this is a read of the\n  caller's own data, matching `GET /v1/usage`'s posture, not `PUT /v1/quotas`'s\n  admin-gated posture). An ingest-scoped key and an admin-scoped key are both\n  authorized identically; neither can pivot to another tenant's data because\n  the endpoint accepts no `customer_id`/`api_key_id` input — the only tenant\n  selector is the authenticated principal itself.\n- No token issuance, no role/permission model change, no widening of what any\n  existing key can reach beyond its own tenant's daily summary.\n\n## Other changes\n\n- `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` — additive only: one new frozen dataclass\n  (`DailyMetricCount`) and one new function (`aggregate_daily_event_counts`)\n  appended at the end of the file; every existing function\n  (`find_usage_rollup`, `count_usage_rollups`, `stream_usage_rollups`) is\n  byte-for-byte unchanged.\n- `src/main.py` — one new import + one new `app.include_router(...)` line;\n  every existing router registration and the middleware stack order are\n  unchanged.\n=== ls .pipeline ===\ntotal 416\ndrwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   512 Jul 11 17:29 .\ndrwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   512 Jul 11 17:09 ..\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett  9374 Jul 11 16:40 acceptance.md\ndrwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   512 Jul  9 16:12 archive\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   116 Jul  9 22:39 asvs-sast.json\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   366 Jul  8 13:28 dast-budget.json\n-rw-r--r-- 1 brett brett 16145 Jul  9 23:51 dast-capture.json\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   322 Jul  9 23:51 dast-review.json\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett  6174 Jul  9 23:51 dast-server.log\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   104 Jul  9 23:50 dast-target-probe.json\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett  1003 Jul  8 13:28 dast.env\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett 10025 Jul 10 01:23 debug-notes.md\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett  2595 Jul 10 00:01 doc-identifiers.json\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root  root  87195 Jul  9 21:56 gitleaks.json\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett 11313 Jul 11 17:24 implementation-progress.md\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett     0 Jul  9 21:54 infra-plan.txt\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   865 Jul 11 17:29 loop-events.jsonl\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   257 Jul 11 17:29 loop-state.json\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett 13016 Jul 10 03:14 m4pp-audit-input.md\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett 17945 Jul 10 03:39 m4pp-audit.md\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   761 Jul 11 17:20 notify-log.jsonl\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   268 Jul  9 22:34 osv.err\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett 18267 Jul  9 22:34 osv.json\n-rwxrwxrwx 1 brett brett   151 Jul 11