\n        text(\n=== scoped_transaction / RLS ===\nsrc/db/session.py:6:transaction that sets `app.current_api_key_id` via `SET LOCAL`, which backs the\nsrc/db/session.py:58:async def scoped_transaction(api_key_id: int) -> AsyncIterator[AsyncSession]:\nsrc/db/session.py:61:    Sets `app.current_api_key_id` with `SET LOCAL` at the start of the\nsrc/db/session.py:77:    \"\"\"Build the `SET LOCAL` statement for the current-tenant RLS setting.\nsrc/db/session.py:79:    A separate function keeps the (slightly unusual) `set_config` call —\nsrc/db/session.py:80:    `SET LOCAL` does not accept a bound parameter directly in all drivers —\nsrc/db/session.py:85:    return text(\"SELECT set_config('app.current_api_key_id', :api_key_id, true)\")","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0321fa29-62fd-4857-a221-d623726c194b","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
