{"parentUuid":"80897a04-205b-415f-9338-40efbf928349","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcvzrXQGB5BcYndDXWuuh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Semgrep now clean: exit 0, scanned exactly my 5 files, 0 results. Let me read the reconcile hook to stamp correctly, and run the remaining required scanners (trivy-fs, and ast-grep — mandatory since the diff touches SQL and async entrypoints)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1132,"cache_read_input_tokens":91282,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1132,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcvzrWUT62MuqJHwn291p","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"6272f2d1-0e4b-49f9-92fe-3f4816bbff15","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:42:26.251Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"6272f2d1-0e4b-49f9-92fe-3f4816bbff15","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcvzrXQGB5BcYndDXWuuh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016Xta7KKUypjF2grDw64BjJ","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat $HOME/.claude/hooks/reconcile-scans.sh 2>/dev/null | head -80; echo \"=== scan-reconciliation.json current ===\"; cat .pipeline/scan-reconciliation.json 2>/dev/null","description":"Read reconcile-scans hook logic"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1132,"cache_read_input_tokens":91282,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1132,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcvzrWUT62MuqJHwn291p","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"8d9eee2e-6eaa-42ad-819b-493979d88b9b","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:42:27.757Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"8d9eee2e-6eaa-42ad-819b-493979d88b9b","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c93d3662-5462-4799-b6d7-cd0b2d4e2c75","agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016Xta7KKUypjF2grDw64BjJ","type":"tool_result","content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# reconcile-scans.sh — U-09: the deterministic teeth behind the security scan counts.\n#\n# The M3 series folded raw scanner JSON into per-tool counts (semgrep_findings,\n# osv_findings, …) with NO independent recount anywhere, and claimed executions whose\n# artifacts were a prior run's or gone. This hook — wired as a security Stop hook —\n# recomputes each per-tool count from the hash-named artifact the agent says it counted,\n# and blocks (exit 2, feeding the model) on any mismatch, so the agent must correct its\n# numbers before it can stop. It is the P0-1 \"stop trusting a summary integer\" pattern\n# applied to the security stage.\n#\n# The agent records, in security-status.json:\n#   \"scan_artifacts\": { \"semgrep\": \"<sha256>\", \"osv\": \"<sha256>\",\n#                       \"trivy\": \"<sha256>\", \"checkov\": \"<sha256>\" }\n# naming the .pipeline/<tool>.json file each pre-fix count was computed from. For each\n# named tool this hook: (1) verifies the artifact exists at .pipeline/<tool>.json and its\n# sha256 matches the claim; (2) verifies a scan-log.jsonl stamp for that tool exists\n# (the execution breadcrumb); (3) RECOMPUTES the count with the R4-validated formula and\n# compares it to the recorded per-tool count. Results go to\n# .pipeline/scan-reconciliation.json (detail) AND `security-status.json.scan_reconciled`\n# (the boolean the deploy gate + loop-exit predicate read — folded into the SAME file\n# the loop-exit security predicate already reads, so loop-exit ≡ gate stays intact,\n# exactly parallel to .asvs.reconciled).\n#\n# NON-GATING by design: stamp FRESHNESS (a carried-forward artifact is legal), and the\n# exploitable/hygiene triage of findings (LLM judgment — P0-3/U-23 evals are the control).\n# Gitleaks is excluded from count reconciliation (its in-scope filtering is triage) but\n# NOT from liveness — it must leave an execution or skip stamp like every scanner (A9).\n#\n# Backward compatible: no scan-log.jsonl (a pre-U-09 project / no wrappers) ⇒ legacy\n# no-op — writes {reconciled:true, legacy:true}, sets no scan_reconciled=false, exit 0.\nset -uo pipefail\n\n[ -f .pipeline/state.json ] || exit 0\ncommand -v jq >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 0\n\nSS=\".pipeline/security-status.json\"\nSCANLOG=\".pipeline/scan-log.jsonl\"\nOUT=\".pipeline/scan-reconciliation.json\"\n\n# --- per-attempt report archiving (U-09) — closes the overwritten-report defect -------\n# security-report.md is overwritten every pass; M3's pass-1/2 reports are unrecoverable.\n# Snapshot the current one to .pipeline/archive/ keyed by this security attempt number\n# (its line count in run-log.jsonl + 1, the same counting log-run.sh uses).\nif [ -f .pipeline/security-report.md ]; then\n  mkdir -p .pipeline/archive\n  _attempt=1\n  if [ -f .pipeline/run-log.jsonl ]; then\n    _prior=\"$(jq -rs 'map(select(.stage==\"security\")) | length' .pipeline/run-log.jsonl 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\"\n    [ -n \"$_prior\" ] && _attempt=$((_prior + 1))\n  fi\n  cp .pipeline/security-report.md \".pipeline/archive/security-report.${_attempt}.md\" 2>/dev/null || true\nfi\n\n# --- legacy no-op: no stamps ⇒ nothing to reconcile -----------------------------------\nif [ ! -f \"$SCANLOG\" ]; then\n  jq -nc '{reconciled:true, legacy:true, ran_at:(now|todateiso8601)}' > \"$OUT\" 2>/dev/null || echo '{\"reconciled\":true,\"legacy\":true}' > \"$OUT\"\n  exit 0\nfi\n\n[ -f \"$SS\" ] || { jq -nc '{reconciled:true, note:\"no security-status.json\"}' > \"$OUT\"; exit 0; }\n\n# Conventional artifact path per tool.\nartifact_path() {\n  case \"$1\" in\n    semgrep) echo \".pipeline/semgrep.json\" ;;\n    osv)     echo \".pipeline/osv.json\" ;;\n    trivy)   echo \".pipeline/trivy-config.json\" ;;\n    checkov) echo \".pipeline/checkov.json\" ;;\n    *)       echo \"\" ;;\n  esac\n}\n\n# R4-validated recount formula per tool (calibrated against the real M3 artifacts).\nrecount() {  # $1 tool, $2 path → integer count, or \"\" if unreadable\n  local tool=\"$1\" p=\"$2\"\n  [ -f \"$p\" ] || { echo \"\"; return; }\n  case \"$tool\" in\n    semgrep) jq -r '(.results // []) | length' \"$p\" 2>/dev/null ;;\n    osv)     jq -r '[.results[]?.packages[]?.vulnerabilities[]?.id] | unique | length' \"$p\" 2>/dev/null ;;\n=== scan-reconciliation.json current ===\n{\"reconciled\":true,\"count_mismatches\":[],\"scope_gaps\":[],\"ran_at\":\"2026-07-10T02:39:06Z\"}","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"531bbedb-0792-4c6a-88bb-6dac53818d1e","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:42:28.378Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# reconcile-scans.sh — U-09: the deterministic teeth behind the security scan counts.\n#\n# The M3 series folded raw scanner JSON into per-tool counts (semgrep_findings,\n# osv_findings, …) with NO independent recount anywhere, and claimed executions whose\n# artifacts were a prior run's or gone. This hook — wired as a security Stop hook —\n# recomputes each per-tool count from the hash-named artifact the agent says it counted,\n# and blocks (exit 2, feeding the model) on any mismatch, so the agent must correct its\n# numbers before it can stop. It is the P0-1 \"stop trusting a summary integer\" pattern\n# applied to the security stage.\n#\n# The agent records, in security-status.json:\n#   \"scan_artifacts\": { \"semgrep\": \"<sha256>\", \"osv\": \"<sha256>\",\n#                       \"trivy\": \"<sha256>\", \"checkov\": \"<sha256>\" }\n# naming the .pipeline/<tool>.json file each pre-fix count was computed from. For each\n# named tool this hook: (1) verifies the artifact exists at .pipeline/<tool>.json and its\n# sha256 matches the claim; (2) verifies a scan-log.jsonl stamp for that tool exists\n# (the execution breadcrumb); (3) RECOMPUTES the count with the R4-validated formula and\n# compares it to the recorded per-tool count. Results go to\n# .pipeline/scan-reconciliation.json (detail) AND `security-status.json.scan_reconciled`\n# (the boolean the deploy gate + loop-exit predicate read — folded into the SAME file\n# the loop-exit security predicate already reads, so loop-exit ≡ gate stays intact,\n# exactly parallel to .asvs.reconciled).\n#\n# NON-GATING by design: stamp FRESHNESS (a carried-forward artifact is legal), and the\n# exploitable/hygiene triage of findings (LLM judgment — P0-3/U-23 evals are the control).\n# Gitleaks is excluded from count reconciliation (its in-scope filtering is triage) but\n# NOT from liveness — it must leave an execution or skip stamp like every scanner (A9).\n#\n# Backward compatible: no scan-log.jsonl (a pre-U-09 project / no wrappers) ⇒ legacy\n# no-op — writes {reconciled:true, legacy:true}, sets no scan_reconciled=false, exit 0.\nset -uo pipefail\n\n[ -f .pipeline/state.json ] || exit 0\ncommand -v jq >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 0\n\nSS=\".pipeline/security-status.json\"\nSCANLOG=\".pipeline/scan-log.jsonl\"\nOUT=\".pipeline/scan-reconciliation.json\"\n\n# --- per-attempt report archiving (U-09) — closes the overwritten-report defect -------\n# security-report.md is overwritten every pass; M3's pass-1/2 reports are unrecoverable.\n# Snapshot the current one to .pipeline/archive/ keyed by this security attempt number\n# (its line count in run-log.jsonl + 1, the same counting log-run.sh uses).\nif [ -f .pipeline/security-report.md ]; then\n  mkdir -p .pipeline/archive\n  _attempt=1\n  if [ -f .pipeline/run-log.jsonl ]; then\n    _prior=\"$(jq -rs 'map(select(.stage==\"security\")) | length' .pipeline/run-log.jsonl 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\"\n    [ -n \"$_prior\" ] && _attempt=$((_prior + 1))\n  fi\n  cp .pipeline/security-report.md \".pipeline/archive/security-report.${_attempt}.md\" 2>/dev/null || true\nfi\n\n# --- legacy no-op: no stamps ⇒ nothing to reconcile -----------------------------------\nif [ ! -f \"$SCANLOG\" ]; then\n  jq -nc '{reconciled:true, legacy:true, ran_at:(now|todateiso8601)}' > \"$OUT\" 2>/dev/null || echo '{\"reconciled\":true,\"legacy\":true}' > \"$OUT\"\n  exit 0\nfi\n\n[ -f \"$SS\" ] || { jq -nc '{reconciled:true, note:\"no security-status.json\"}' > \"$OUT\"; exit 0; }\n\n# Conventional artifact path per tool.\nartifact_path() {\n  case \"$1\" in\n    semgrep) echo \".pipeline/semgrep.json\" ;;\n    osv)     echo \".pipeline/osv.json\" ;;\n    trivy)   echo \".pipeline/trivy-config.json\" ;;\n    checkov) echo \".pipeline/checkov.json\" ;;\n    *)       echo \"\" ;;\n  esac\n}\n\n# R4-validated recount formula per tool (calibrated against the real M3 artifacts).\nrecount() {  # $1 tool, $2 path → integer count, or \"\" if unreadable\n  local tool=\"$1\" p=\"$2\"\n  [ -f \"$p\" ] || { echo \"\"; return; }\n  case \"$tool\" in\n    semgrep) jq -r '(.results // []) | length' \"$p\" 2>/dev/null ;;\n    osv)     jq -r '[.results[]?.packages[]?.vulnerabilities[]?.id] | unique | length' \"$p\" 2>/dev/null ;;\n=== scan-reconciliation.json current ===\n{\"reconciled\":true,\"count_mismatches\":[],\"scope_gaps\":[],\"ran_at\":\"2026-07-10T02:39:06Z\"}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8d9eee2e-6eaa-42ad-819b-493979d88b9b","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"531bbedb-0792-4c6a-88bb-6dac53818d1e","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcvzrXQGB5BcYndDXWuuh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01AwqVMqHeCWH2JfrFHKF6g8","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test\necho \"=== ast-grep over change-set (SQL + async triggers) ===\"\n$HOME/.claude/hooks/ast-grep-scan.sh 2>&1 | head -40; echo \"ast-grep exit=$?\"","description":"Run ast-grep rules pack"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1132,"cache_read_input_tokens":91282,"output_tokens":1139,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1132},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1139,"cache_read_input_tokens":91282,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1132,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1132,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcvzrWUT62MuqJHwn291p","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"8de9c4f7-07fb-4232-9e63-7bd6228a602e","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:42:29.137Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"8de9c4f7-07fb-4232-9e63-7bd6228a602e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c93d3662-5462-4799-b6d7-cd0b2d4e2c75","agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AwqVMqHeCWH2JfrFHKF6g8","type":"tool_result","content":"=== ast-grep over change-set (SQL + async triggers) ===\nSearch and Rewrite code at large scale using precise AST pattern\n\nUsage: ast-grep [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>\n\nCommands:\n  run          Run one time search or rewrite in command line. (default command)\n  scan         Scan and rewrite code by configuration\n  test         Test ast-grep rules\n  new          Create new ast-grep project or items like rules/tests\n  lsp          Start language server\n  outline      Explore code structure for symbols, imports, exports, and members\n  completions  Generate shell completion script\n  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)\n\nOptions:\n  -c, --config <CONFIG_FILE>  Path to ast-grep root config, default is sgconfig.yml\n  -h, --help                  Print help (see more with '--help')\n  -V, --version               Print version\nast-grep exit=0","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"2a9a8b24-f5eb-47d7-bb7c-f092962325ad","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:42:33.490Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"=== ast-grep over change-set (SQL + async triggers) ===\nSearch and Rewrite code at large scale using precise AST pattern\n\nUsage: ast-grep [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>\n\nCommands:\n  run          Run one time search or rewrite in command line. (default command)\n  scan         Scan and rewrite code by configuration\n  test         Test ast-grep rules\n  new          Create new ast-grep project or items like rules/tests\n  lsp          Start language server\n  outline      Explore code structure for symbols, imports, exports, and members\n  completions  Generate shell completion script\n  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)\n\nOptions:\n  -c, --config <CONFIG_FILE>  Path to ast-grep root config, default is sgconfig.yml\n  -h, --help                  Print help (see more with '--help')\n  -V, --version               Print version\nast-grep exit=0","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8de9c4f7-07fb-4232-9e63-7bd6228a602e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
