run) — a never-ran scanner is not 0 findings; write null or run the scan (A9)\" \\\n      '. + [{tool:$t, reason:$r}]')\"\n  fi\ndone\n\nREQUIRED=\"semgrep osv gitleaks\"\nDIFF_REF=\"HEAD\"; git rev-parse --verify -q HEAD >/dev/null 2>&1 || DIFF_REF=\"\"\nCHANGED=\"$( { [ -n \"$DIFF_REF\" ] && git diff \"$DIFF_REF\" --name-only 2>/dev/null; \\\n              git ls-files --others --exclude-standard 2>/dev/null; } | sort -u )\"\nprintf '%s\\n' \"$CHANGED\" | grep -qE '^infra/' && REQUIRED=\"$REQUIRED checkov\"\nprintf '%s\\n' \"$CHANGED\" | grep -qE '(^|/)Dockerfile' && REQUIRED=\"$REQUIRED trivy\"\nfor tool in $REQUIRED; do\n  if ! has_stamp \"$tool\"; then\n    MISMATCHES=\"$(printf '%s' \"$MISMATCHES\" | jq -c --arg t \"$tool\" \\\n      --arg r \"required scanner $tool has no execution or skip stamp this run — run it through its wrapper, or let the wrapper stamp the disclosed skip (A9 liveness)\" \\\n      '. + [{tool:$t, reason:$r}]')\"\n  fi\ndone\n\n# Scope reconciliation: every code-shaped changed file should appear in a this-run semgrep\n# stamp's paths.scanned when available. If semgrep.json carries `.paths.scanned`, check it;\n# absent that field, skip (older semgrep output / not a full-tree scan) rather than false-block.\nSCOPE_GAPS='[]'\nSEMGREP_P=\"$(artifact_path semgrep)\"\nif [ -f \"$SEMGREP_P\" ] && jq -e '.paths.scanned' \"$SEMGREP_P\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n  # Only consider changed files with a CODE shape Semgrep is EXPECTED to scan — a positive\n  # ALLOWLIST, not a blocklist. An exclusion blocklist would false-block on any unusual\n  # extension Semgrep legitimately doesn't scan (a .toml/.cfg/.ini, a dependency-only\n  # pyproject bump): it lands in \"changed but not scanned\" → a spurious scope gap →\n  # scan_reconciled=false → a WRONGLY blocked clean deploy. Allowlisting the shapes Semgrep\n  # covers (py/js/ts/go/java/rb/php/tf/yaml/json/dockerfile/bash — matching its own language\n  # set) means an unknown extension is simply not checked here, never a false gap.\n  CODE_INCLUDE='\\.(py|js|jsx|ts|tsx|go|java|rb|php|tf|ya?ml|sh|bash)$|(^|/)Dockerfile$'\n  DIFF_REF=\"HEAD\"; git rev-parse --verify -q HEAD >/dev/null 2>&1 || DIFF_REF=\"\"\n  { [ -n \"$DIFF_REF\" ] && git diff \"$DIFF_REF\" --name-only 2>/dev/null; \\\n    git ls-files --others --exclude-standard 2>/dev/null; } \\\n    | grep -vE '(^|/)\\.pipeline/' | grep -E \"$CODE_INCLUDE\" | sort -u > \"/tmp/.u09_changed.$$\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  jq -r '.paths.scanned[]?' \"$SEMGREP_P\" 2>/dev/null | sed 's#^\\./##' | sort -u > \"/tmp/.u09_scanned.$$\" 2>/dev/null || true\n  while IFS= read -r f; do\n    [ -n \"$f\" ] || continue\n    grep -qxF \"$f\" \"/tmp/.u09_scanned.$$\" 2>/dev/null || \\\n      SCOPE_GAPS=\"$(printf '%s' \"$SCOPE_GAPS\" | jq -c --arg f \"$f\" '. + [$f]')\"\n  done < \"/tmp/.u09_changed.$$\"\n  rm -f \"/tmp/.u09_changed.$$\" \"/tmp/.u09_scanned.$$\" 2>/dev/null || true\nfi\n\nRECONCILED=true\n[ \"$(printf '%s' \"$MISMATCHES\" | jq 'length')\" -gt 0 ] && RECONCILED=false\n[ \"$(printf '%s' \"$SCOPE_GAPS\" | jq 'length')\" -gt 0 ] && RECONCILED=false\n\njq -nc --argjson mm \"$MISMATCHES\" --argjson sg \"$SCOPE_GAPS\" --argjson rec \"$RECONCILED\" \\\n  --arg t \"$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)\" \\\n  '{reconciled:$rec, count_mismatches:$mm, scope_gaps:$sg, ran_at:$t}' > \"$OUT\"\n\n# Fold the boolean into security-status.json for the gate + loop-exit predicate (same file\n# the loop-exit security predicate reads → loop-exit ≡ gate preserved, parallel to asvs).\ntmp=\"$(mktemp)\"; jq --argjson r \"$RECONCILED\" '.scan_reconciled = $r' \"$SS\" > \"$tmp\" 2>/dev/null && mv \"$tmp\" \"$SS\" || rm -f \"$tmp\"\n\nif [ \"$RECONCILED\" = \"false\" ]; then","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"cb5e0a34-8e8b-4144-b681-26d57d1ae47c","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"fd4167f0-40d7-4001-86b8-937d0548b6cd","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c93d3662-5462-4799-b6d7-cd0b2d4e2c75","agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_015oumM1P15G94dZ5wW4wn58","content":"Launching skill: ast-grep-rules"}]},"uuid":"52ca8067-bb72-4cb2-9994-bb50e17a5b09","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:42:41.256Z","toolUseResult":{"success":true,"commandName":"ast-grep-rules"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"fd4167f0-40d7-4001-86b8-937d0548b6cd","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"52ca8067-bb72-4cb2-9994-bb50e17a5b09","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c93d3662-5462-4799-b6d7-cd0b2d4e2c75","agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Base directory for this skill: /mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.claude/skills/ast-grep-rules\n\n<!-- loading: on-demand (invoked via the Skill tool when needed) — generated by scripts/list-skills.sh --annotate; do not hand-edit -->\n\n# ast-grep structural rules (project template)\n\n> **Project-scoped template.** Copy the rules you want into the project, adapt the\n> language/pattern, then commit. ast-grep is an **optional adjunct** to Semgrep/OSV/Trivy,\n> not a replacement — it shines at structural patterns that are awkward as regex.\n\n## When to use it\n\nInvoke `ast-grep` (CLI, `Bash(ast-grep:*)`) when a STRIDE efficacy question (U-02) or a\ndiff review needs a *syntax-shaped* check that a text regex would get wrong — e.g. \"is a\nCPU-hard call on the async event loop\", \"is this RLS policy created without FORCE\". It\nparses to an AST, so it does not false-match inside strings/comments the way `grep` does.\n\n## Advisory-only contract (hard boundary)\n\nast-grep findings go into **`security-report.md` prose only**. They **must NOT** feed any\n`security-status.json` count (`semgrep_findings`, `critical_count`, …) or any gate/loop-exit\nconjunct. Reason: unlike the wrapped scanners (U-09 stamps + `reconcile-scans.sh`\nrecomputes their counts from hash-verified artifacts), ast-grep has **no wrapper and no\ncount reconciliation yet**. Until it gets one (TA A-4 backlog), an ast-grep hit is a\n*lead to investigate*, never a number the gate trusts. If a hit reveals a real defect, the\nfix flows through the normal exploitable-finding path and shows up in the reconciled tools'\ncounts on the next scan.\n\n## Example rules (starter set — adapt per stack)\n\n### R1 — sync KDF / blocking call on the async event loop (Python)\nPairs with the async-runtime efficacy question. Flags a bcrypt/argon2/scrypt call made\ndirectly inside an `async def` (should be off-loaded to a thread pool).\n```yaml\nid: sync-kdf-in-async\nlanguage: python\nrule:\n  inside: { kind: function_definition, has: { field: async, regex: \"async\" } }\n  pattern: $HASHER.$METHOD($$$)\nconstraints:\n  HASHER: { regex: \"bcrypt|argon2|scrypt|pbkdf2\" }\nnote: CPU-hard KDF on the event loop blocks all concurrent requests — run it in a thread pool.\n```\n\n### R2 — RLS policy created without FORCE (SQL)\nPairs with the DB-privilege efficacy question. A table-owning role bypasses RLS unless the\ntable is `FORCE`d; a `CREATE POLICY` with no accompanying `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` is a\nlead to check ownership.\n```yaml\nid: rls-without-force\nlanguage: sql\nrule:\n  pattern: CREATE POLICY $$$\nnote: If the app role owns this table, RLS is advisory without ALTER TABLE ... FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY — verify ownership.\n```\n\n## Running\n\n```\nast-grep scan --rule <rule>.yml <path>      # one rule\nast-grep scan --config sgconfig.yml <path>  # a project rule set\n```\nRoute any raw output you keep to `.pipeline/` (never the tree/scratchpad), same as the\nother scanners. It does not need Docker — it is a single native binary.\n"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"82adf014-756f-40ff-a5af-2ec5ea0fa226","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:42:41.255Z","sourceToolUseID":"toolu_015oumM1P15G94dZ5wW4wn58","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
