{"parentUuid":"13ff9703-c701-458c-a50a-6b99b326df89","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c93d3662-5462-4799-b6d7-cd0b2d4e2c75","agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CymUaEHUZGg4zyfuUpVqWR","type":"tool_result","content":"=== gitleaks tests/ and docs/ hits (are they change-set files?) ===\ndocs/decisions/feature/usage-export/security-report.md:125 generic-api-key\ntests/test_schemas_events.py:18 generic-api-key\ntests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py:117 generic-api-key\n=== my new test files, for comparison ===\ntests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py  tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py\n=== acceptance.md input/data criteria quick check ===\n6:  - \"GET /v1/usage/daily (query param: date) — validation = AC3+AC4+AC5+AC6; rate-limit = AC13\"\n17:**rate-limit** criterion is **AC13**. Validation is not waived (untrusted internet input).\n33:| AC13 | **Rate-limit (input-surface):** the route is behind the **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** token-bucket throttle (post-auth, principal-keyed) plus the **Tier-1** IP+route edge throttle — reused, not reinvented. Key dimension = `api_key_id`; limit = `principal.rate_limit_per_sec`; window = token bucket. | `routes/usage_daily.py` (`enforce_tier2_rate_limit`), `main.py` (`Tier1EdgeThrottleMiddleware`) | The route's dependency chain includes `_require_authenticated_and_throttled` (auth→Tier-2), identical to the sibling routes; the existing two-principals-one-IP Tier-2 test (`tests/integration/test_rate_limit.py`) proves the principal-keyed mechanism. Assert the daily route resolves the Tier-2 dependency (`test_usage_daily_endpoint.py::test_route_behind_tier2_throttle`). |\n41:  security/tenant-isolation, boundary, logging, rate-limit, DAST, and safe-error criteria","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"cf148fa1-db2f-45af-8eaa-e0d4de175f98","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:47:23.009Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"=== gitleaks tests/ and docs/ hits (are they change-set files?) ===\ndocs/decisions/feature/usage-export/security-report.md:125 generic-api-key\ntests/test_schemas_events.py:18 generic-api-key\ntests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py:117 generic-api-key\n=== my new test files, for comparison ===\ntests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py  tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py\n=== acceptance.md input/data criteria quick check ===\n6:  - \"GET /v1/usage/daily (query param: date) — validation = AC3+AC4+AC5+AC6; rate-limit = AC13\"\n17:**rate-limit** criterion is **AC13**. Validation is not waived (untrusted internet input).\n33:| AC13 | **Rate-limit (input-surface):** the route is behind the **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** token-bucket throttle (post-auth, principal-keyed) plus the **Tier-1** IP+route edge throttle — reused, not reinvented. Key dimension = `api_key_id`; limit = `principal.rate_limit_per_sec`; window = token bucket. | `routes/usage_daily.py` (`enforce_tier2_rate_limit`), `main.py` (`Tier1EdgeThrottleMiddleware`) | The route's dependency chain includes `_require_authenticated_and_throttled` (auth→Tier-2), identical to the sibling routes; the existing two-principals-one-IP Tier-2 test (`tests/integration/test_rate_limit.py`) proves the principal-keyed mechanism. Assert the daily route resolves the Tier-2 dependency (`test_usage_daily_endpoint.py::test_route_behind_tier2_throttle`). |\n41:  security/tenant-isolation, boundary, logging, rate-limit, DAST, and safe-error criteria","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"13ff9703-c701-458c-a50a-6b99b326df89","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
