{"parentUuid":"e436ace4-fd7b-45e1-bdb7-ffacbd2e07df","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccw1FUPpuJyhXgg9weTbu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirmed: the tests/docs gitleaks hits are all in **old** files (test_schemas_events.py, test_usage_export_endpoint.py, usage-export docs) — none in my new test files. Zero secrets in the change-set. acceptance.md confirms the input-surface controls (validation AC3-6 + Tier-2 rate-limit AC13) and no stored-data criteria. Now writing both artifacts."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4369,"cache_read_input_tokens":116493,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4369,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccw1FT8gMuEKgJcQYAA7K","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"eff0d19a-3532-449c-9637-91863f3f15ff","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:47:50.634Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"eff0d19a-3532-449c-9637-91863f3f15ff","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccw1FUPpuJyhXgg9weTbu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Mmx7mWNjty18eekdFHznwD","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-report.md","content":"---\nstatus: issues-found\nran_at: 2026-07-11T21:30:09Z\nscope: diff\nsince_commit: 791a37c903a0420cfa81ec90e35cdbfe74dc9443\ncritical_count: 1\nwarning_count: 0\nfixed_count: 0\ntotal_findings: 2\nsemgrep_findings: 0\nosv_findings: 0\ncheckov_findings: null\ntrivy_findings: null\nstride_mechanisms_verified: 7\nstride_mechanisms_missing: 1\nstride_new_threats: 0\n---\n\n# Security report — `usage-daily` (`GET /v1/usage/daily`)\n\nScope: working-tree change set since `791a37c` (diff-scoping-conventions). Additive\ncustomer-scoped read endpoint. Files scanned:\n\n- NEW: `src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`, `src/services/usage_daily_service.py`,\n  `src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`, `tests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py`,\n  `tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py`\n- MODIFIED (additive): `src/main.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`\n\n## Bottom line\n\nThe new endpoint's own code is clean: SQL is fully parameterized/bound, the `date` input\nis validated by an anchored ReDoS-safe allowlist, the tenant predicate is `api_key_id`-first\nfrom the authenticated principal, errors fail closed, and no secrets/new dependencies were\nintroduced. **One blocking critical remains** — the RLS backstop the plan names as a\ndefense-in-depth control for the IDOR threat is **inert for the application role** (a\npre-existing migration-0002 gap). The primary app-level tenant predicate is present and\ncorrect, so the endpoint is **not independently exploitable** for cross-tenant reads, but\nper the presence-is-not-efficacy rule (U-02) a named-but-inert security mechanism is a\ncritical and is routed to remediation.\n\n## Tools run\n\n| Tool | Result | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Semgrep (native 1.169.0, `p/secrets` + `p/owasp-top-ten` + `p/python` + `p/default`, 1145 rules) | 0 findings | Scanned exactly the 5 change-set code files; clean. The Docker wrapper could not run — its container cannot resolve `semgrep.dev` (offline registry). Ran the **native** binary instead (host resolves fine). `.pipeline/semgrep.json`. |\n| OSV Scanner | 0 unfiltered (1 filtered/waived) | Scanned `poetry.lock` (80 pkgs). Only finding = `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest 8.3.4, CVSS 6.8 Medium, dev-only), **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` (below the 7.0 gate floor; not in the deployed surface). No new dependency introduced by this feature. `.pipeline/osv.json`. |\n| Gitleaks | 0 in change-set | 128 tree-wide hits, all in `.venv/` (vendored botocore data), `.pipeline/archive/`, `docs/`, and pre-existing test fixtures (`test_schemas_events.py`, `test_usage_export_endpoint.py`) — **none** in any change-set file. `.pipeline/gitleaks.json`. |\n| lockfile-check (supply-chain) | clean | No manifest/lockfile drift; no unpinned specifiers. |\n| asvs-sast (Tier-1) | 0 critical, 0 warning | No JWT-none / fast-hash / non-CSPRNG / weak-cipher in the diff. |\n| ast-grep (structural, advisory-only) | 1 hit, pre-existing | See \"ast-grep\" below. |\n| Trivy fs / config | skipped (disclosed) | Docker DNS unreachable (`mirror.gcr.io`) — vuln DB pull failed. Not a required scanner (no Dockerfile in change-set); OSV covered SCA. |\n| Checkov | not run (n/a) | No `infra/` change in the change-set. |\n\n## Complete findings inventory\n\n| # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | manual-6d | STRIDE-efficacy: `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS backstop inert for app role (owner, no FORCE) | critical (per U-02) | no (primary app predicate present; no object-id input) | `alembic/versions/0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py:67-73` (+ runtime owner in `src/db/session.py`) | could-not-remediate |\n| 2 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g (PYSEC-2026-1845, pytest 8.3.4) | medium (CVSS 6.8) | no (dev-only, not in prod container) | `poetry.lock` | reported-only (waived, `osv-scanner.toml`) |\n\n`total_findings = 2`. Semgrep, gitleaks (in-scope), lockfile-check, asvs-sast, and manual\nchecks 6a/6c/6e/6f/6g each produced **0** findings, so contribute no rows.\n\n## Critical finding detail (row 1)\n\n**STRIDE mitigation ineffective — RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`.**\n\nThe plan's Information-Disclosure (IDOR) mitigation claims: *\"plus RLS policy\n`usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` (migration 0002) **enforced** via `SET LOCAL\napp.current_api_key_id`.\"* That claim is false for the application role:\n\n- Migration `0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py` runs `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup ENABLE\n  ROW LEVEL SECURITY` and `CREATE POLICY usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` but **does not**\n  run `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`.\n- Migrations execute as `meterly_app` (per `0003`'s own comment: the migration job resolves\n  the DB URL through the same secrets facade the app uses → the `meterly_app` credential),\n  so `meterly_app` **owns** `usage_rollup`. The runtime app also connects as `meterly_app`.\n- In PostgreSQL, a **table owner bypasses non-FORCE RLS** regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS`. So\n  the policy is inert for the app role — the backstop does not fire.\n- This is confirmed by the codebase's own intent: migration `0003` applies `ALTER TABLE\n  quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` with a comment documenting exactly this owner-bypass\n  semantics. `0001` (events) and `0002` (usage_rollup) omit it — an inconsistency/oversight,\n  not a deliberate exception.\n\n**Why it is not independently exploitable through this feature:** the primary tenant control\nis present and correct — `aggregate_daily_event_counts` (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`)\nuses `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` as its **first** predicate, bound from\n`principal.api_key_id` (never client input), and the endpoint accepts **no** `customer_id` /\n`api_key_id` parameter (`extra=\"forbid\"`), so there is no IDOR selector. Cross-tenant reads\nare blocked at the application layer today. The finding is that the *defense-in-depth\nbackstop* — the layer meant to catch a future missing-predicate bug — is silently disabled.\n\n**Verified-safe remediation (for the remediation/debugging role):** add a new forward\nmigration `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`:\n- upgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`\n- downgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup NO FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`\n- `down_revision` chained to `0003`.\n\nThis is **behavior-preserving**: I verified that **every runtime reader/writer of\n`usage_rollup` executes inside `scoped_transaction`** (which sets `app.current_api_key_id`\nvia `SET LOCAL`) — the four services `usage_daily`, `usage_export`, `quota`\n(`read_tenant_quota_state_locked`), and `events` (the rollup increment) all do. Under FORCE\neach still sees exactly the rows the app predicate already returns, so no legitimate query\nresult changes. (The 0002 backfill `INSERT…SELECT` ran as owner without the GUC, but that\ncompletes before 0004 enables FORCE, so it is unaffected.) The migration should ship with a\nfails-before/passes-after tenant-isolation test proving a query with the GUC unset returns\nzero rows — which is why this is routed to the remediation role (schema change + test)\nrather than patched inline by the security stage, consistent with how gating dependency\nbumps are routed (U-19/D2).\n\n**Related observation (out of change-set scope, not counted):** migration `0001` gives the\n`events` table the same latent gap (ENABLE without FORCE, owner = app role). The FORCE\nmigration should cover `events` too for consistency; flagged here for the remediation role's\nawareness though `events` is outside this feature's surface.\n\n## Fixes applied\n\nNone. The new endpoint code required no changes (clean). The single critical is a\nschema-migration remediation routed to the remediation/debugging role (see above), so\n`fixed_count = 0`.\n\n## Could not remediate — human/remediation review required\n\n- **Row 1 (RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`).** Requires a new alembic migration +\n  isolation test; routed to the remediation role. Exact verified-safe recipe above.\n\n## Action required\n\n- **OSV `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest → 9.0.3).** Below the CVSS 7.0 gate floor (6.8),\n  dev-only, and **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` with a review date\n  (`ignoreUntil = 2026-10-09`). No action this cycle; the major-version bump (pytest 8→9)\n  is tracked as a deliberate dev-dependency upgrade. Not introduced by this feature.\n\n## STRIDE mechanism verification (6d)\n\n8 named threats in `plan.md`; 7 mechanisms present-and-effective, 1 present-but-inert.\n\n| Threat | Mechanism | Evidence | Status |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Spoofing (auth) | `require_api_key` composed in `_require_authenticated_and_throttled` | `routes/usage_daily.py:23-30,36` | ✓ effective |\n| Tampering (`date` injection) | anchored `^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$` + `date.fromisoformat` + `[now-90d,now+1d]` → 400; value never reaches SQL as text (bound `:day_start/:day_end`) | `schemas/usage_daily.py:24,80-102`; `usage_repo.py:229-243` | ✓ effective |\n| Tampering (param smuggling) | `DailyUsageQueryParams(extra=\"forbid\")` | `schemas/usage_daily.py:44,46` | ✓ effective |\n| Repudiation | `logger.info(\"usage.daily.read\", …)` (no values, only counts) | `usage_daily_service.py:46-53` | ✓ effective |\n| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — primary | `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` first predicate, from principal; no object-id input | `usage_repo.py:236`; `routes/usage_daily.py` | ✓ effective |\n| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — backstop | `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS via `SET LOCAL` | migration `0002:67-73` | ✗ **inert (owner, no FORCE)** — row 1 |\n| Info Disclosure (error leak) | central `handle_unexpected_error` generic 500; service adds no try/except; `DailyUsageResponse(extra=\"forbid\")` | `api/errors.py:97-116`; `usage_daily_service.py`; `schemas/usage_daily.py:119-122` | ✓ effective |\n| DoS | Tier-2 `enforce_tier2_rate_limit` (redis token bucket, principal-keyed post-auth) + Tier-1 edge + date bound + single-day GROUP BY | `auth/rate_limit.py:136`; `routes/usage_daily.py:29` | ✓ effective |\n| EoP | `require_api_key` only, no admin gate needed, no object-id → no pivot | `routes/usage_daily.py:36` | ✓ effective |\n\nEfficacy answers (U-02): topology — Tier-2 runs **after** auth so it is principal-keyed not\nIP-keyed (✓); DB privilege — RLS owner check → **inert without FORCE** (✗, the critical);\nasync runtime — no CPU-hard/blocking sync calls in the async handlers (✓); contract drift —\nerror scrubber owns every error body, log facade strips control chars (✓).\n\n## STRIDE delta / attack-surface reconciliation (6f)\n\n`stride_new_threats: 0`. New surface introduced by the diff = the `GET /v1/usage/daily`\nroute, the `aggregate_daily_event_counts` read query, and the `usage.daily.read` log event.\nEvery one is covered by an existing `plan.md` threat-model entry (verified against\n`surface-delta.md`, which matched the diff). No new outbound calls, subprocess, SSRF sink,\nstored data, or privilege surface. No uncovered surface → no addendum entries. (The RLS\ninefficacy is an *efficacy* finding on an existing mitigation, 6d, not a new-surface gap.)\n\n## ast-grep (structural, advisory-only — not counted)\n\nRan the SQL/async structural checks (F-M4-5 trigger: diff touches SQL + async entrypoints).\nOne hit: `text(f\"…\")` at `usage_repo.py:134` — this is `count_usage_rollups`, a\n**pre-existing, byte-for-byte-unchanged** function (diff hunks are lines 1-5 and 198-248\nonly), already triaged with a `nosemgrep` pragma and a fixed-literal (non-client) WHERE\nclause. The **new** `aggregate_daily_event_counts` uses a plain bound-param `text(\"\"\"…\"\"\")`\nwith no interpolation — clean. No blocking-call/KDF-on-event-loop hits. Advisory only; feeds\nno count.\n\n## ASVS 5.0.0 (6g)\n\nTriggered chapters (from plan `## ASVS Compliance`): V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V11, V13, V16.\nL1/L2 verified universally; no new in-scope L3 (reused Argon2id path's 11.2.4 already met).\n\n- V1 (parameterized SQL): bound params, no interpolation of caller input — met.\n- V2 (validation + anti-automation): `parse_daily_date` allowlist + Tier-1/Tier-2 throttle — met.\n- V6 (auth): `require_api_key` reused — met.\n- V8 (8.2.2 object-level authz / tenant isolation): met **at the application layer** by the\n  `api_key_id`-first predicate + no object-id input. The RLS defense-in-depth backstop is\n  degraded (row 1) — surfaced once as the 6d critical, not double-counted here.\n- V11 (crypto): reused Argon2id key verification — met.\n- V13 (config / least-privilege): app role `NOBYPASSRLS` (infra) — met; the FORCE gap is the\n  6d finding.\n- V16 (logging & error handling): structured `usage.daily.read`, no PII/values/raw body;\n  fail-closed central error envelope — met.\n\n`asvs.reconciled: true` — no unmet/​unwaived code/config L1/L2 or in-scope-L3 item (the ASVS\nobject-authz requirement is satisfied by the present primary control; the inert RLS backstop\nis captured as the 6d critical that already flips `status` to issues-found).\n\n## Input / data surface reconciliation\n\n- **input_surface** — 1 implemented source (`GET /v1/usage/daily?date=…`), with BOTH a\n  validation contract (`DailyUsageQueryParams` + `parse_daily_date`, acceptance AC3-6) AND a\n  rate-limit policy (Tier-2 principal-keyed + Tier-1, acceptance AC13). `uncontrolled: []`,\n  reconciled.\n- **data_surface** — pure read; the diff stores no new field/table/column/cache/blob.\n  `classified: 0`, `unprotected: []`, reconciled. (`data-protection-conventions` not\n  triggered — `usage_rollup` was classified non-sensitive operational metering data by the\n  prior feature.)\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4369,"cache_read_input_tokens":116493,"output_tokens":7792,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4369},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":7792,"cache_read_input_tokens":116493,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4369,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4369,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccw1FT8gMuEKgJcQYAA7K","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"04527389-89d3-4632-802b-1c54f610e363","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:49:04.881Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
