{"parentUuid":"488f5f2a-81dd-4733-86d1-7e4192002e61","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccw1PS59sxqeLrN742vYL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Stale quota-admin report confirmed. Now overwriting both artifacts."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":192,"cache_read_input_tokens":128697,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":192,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccw1PQdavDi2D6ThivqSd","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"7decad0b-587c-4e3b-9405-7c98f5c96126","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:49:13.599Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"7decad0b-587c-4e3b-9405-7c98f5c96126","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccw1PS59sxqeLrN742vYL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NwCcuWyQiN2xB835uPQD9v","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-report.md","content":"---\nstatus: issues-found\nran_at: 2026-07-11T21:30:09Z\nscope: diff\nsince_commit: 791a37c903a0420cfa81ec90e35cdbfe74dc9443\ncritical_count: 1\nwarning_count: 0\nfixed_count: 0\ntotal_findings: 2\nsemgrep_findings: 0\nosv_findings: 0\ncheckov_findings: null\ntrivy_findings: null\nstride_mechanisms_verified: 7\nstride_mechanisms_missing: 1\nstride_new_threats: 0\n---\n\n# Security report — `usage-daily` (`GET /v1/usage/daily`)\n\nScope: working-tree change set since `791a37c` (diff-scoping-conventions). Additive\ncustomer-scoped read endpoint. Files scanned:\n\n- NEW: `src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`, `src/services/usage_daily_service.py`,\n  `src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`, `tests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py`,\n  `tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py`\n- MODIFIED (additive): `src/main.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`\n\n## Bottom line\n\nThe new endpoint's own code is clean: SQL is fully parameterized/bound, the `date` input\nis validated by an anchored ReDoS-safe allowlist, the tenant predicate is `api_key_id`-first\nfrom the authenticated principal, errors fail closed, and no secrets/new dependencies were\nintroduced. **One blocking critical remains** — the RLS backstop the plan names as a\ndefense-in-depth control for the IDOR threat is **inert for the application role** (a\npre-existing migration-0002 gap). The primary app-level tenant predicate is present and\ncorrect, so the endpoint is **not independently exploitable** for cross-tenant reads, but\nper the presence-is-not-efficacy rule (U-02) a named-but-inert security mechanism is a\ncritical and is routed to remediation.\n\n## Tools run\n\n| Tool | Result | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Semgrep (native 1.169.0, `p/secrets` + `p/owasp-top-ten` + `p/python` + `p/default`, 1145 rules) | 0 findings | Scanned exactly the 5 change-set code files; clean. The Docker wrapper could not run — its container cannot resolve `semgrep.dev` (offline registry). Ran the **native** binary instead (host resolves fine). `.pipeline/semgrep.json`. |\n| OSV Scanner | 0 unfiltered (1 filtered/waived) | Scanned `poetry.lock` (80 pkgs). Only finding = `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest 8.3.4, CVSS 6.8 Medium, dev-only), **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` (below the 7.0 gate floor; not in the deployed surface). No new dependency introduced by this feature. `.pipeline/osv.json`. |\n| Gitleaks | 0 in change-set | 128 tree-wide hits, all in `.venv/` (vendored botocore data), `.pipeline/archive/`, `docs/`, and pre-existing test fixtures (`test_schemas_events.py`, `test_usage_export_endpoint.py`) — **none** in any change-set file. `.pipeline/gitleaks.json`. |\n| lockfile-check (supply-chain) | clean | No manifest/lockfile drift; no unpinned specifiers. |\n| asvs-sast (Tier-1) | 0 critical, 0 warning | No JWT-none / fast-hash / non-CSPRNG / weak-cipher in the diff. |\n| ast-grep (structural, advisory-only) | 1 hit, pre-existing | See \"ast-grep\" below. |\n| Trivy fs / config | skipped (disclosed) | Docker DNS unreachable (`mirror.gcr.io`) — vuln DB pull failed. Not a required scanner (no Dockerfile in change-set); OSV covered SCA. |\n| Checkov | not run (n/a) | No `infra/` change in the change-set. |\n\n## Complete findings inventory\n\n| # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | manual-6d | STRIDE-efficacy: `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS backstop inert for app role (owner, no FORCE) | critical (per U-02) | no (primary app predicate present; no object-id input) | `alembic/versions/0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py:67-73` (+ runtime owner in `src/db/session.py`) | could-not-remediate |\n| 2 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g (PYSEC-2026-1845, pytest 8.3.4) | medium (CVSS 6.8) | no (dev-only, not in prod container) | `poetry.lock` | reported-only (waived, `osv-scanner.toml`) |\n\n`total_findings = 2`. Semgrep, gitleaks (in-scope), lockfile-check, asvs-sast, and manual\nchecks 6a/6c/6e/6f/6g each produced **0** findings, so contribute no rows.\n\n## Critical finding detail (row 1)\n\n**STRIDE mitigation ineffective — RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`.**\n\nThe plan's Information-Disclosure (IDOR) mitigation claims: *\"plus RLS policy\n`usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` (migration 0002) **enforced** via `SET LOCAL\napp.current_api_key_id`.\"* That claim is false for the application role:\n\n- Migration `0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py` runs `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup ENABLE\n  ROW LEVEL SECURITY` and `CREATE POLICY usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` but **does not**\n  run `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`.\n- Migrations execute as `meterly_app` (per `0003`'s own comment: the migration job resolves\n  the DB URL through the same secrets facade the app uses → the `meterly_app` credential),\n  so `meterly_app` **owns** `usage_rollup`. The runtime app also connects as `meterly_app`.\n- In PostgreSQL, a **table owner bypasses non-FORCE RLS** regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS`. So\n  the policy is inert for the app role — the backstop does not fire.\n- This is confirmed by the codebase's own intent: migration `0003` applies `ALTER TABLE\n  quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` with a comment documenting exactly this owner-bypass\n  semantics. `0001` (events) and `0002` (usage_rollup) omit it — an inconsistency/oversight,\n  not a deliberate exception.\n\n**Why it is not independently exploitable through this feature:** the primary tenant control\nis present and correct — `aggregate_daily_event_counts` (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`)\nuses `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` as its **first** predicate, bound from\n`principal.api_key_id` (never client input), and the endpoint accepts **no** `customer_id` /\n`api_key_id` parameter (`extra=\"forbid\"`), so there is no IDOR selector. Cross-tenant reads\nare blocked at the application layer today. The finding is that the *defense-in-depth\nbackstop* — the layer meant to catch a future missing-predicate bug — is silently disabled.\n\n**Verified-safe remediation (for the remediation/debugging role):** add a new forward\nmigration `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`:\n- upgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`\n- downgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup NO FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`\n- `down_revision` chained to `0003`.\n\nThis is **behavior-preserving**: I verified that **every runtime reader/writer of\n`usage_rollup` executes inside `scoped_transaction`** (which sets `app.current_api_key_id`\nvia `SET LOCAL`) — the four services `usage_daily`, `usage_export`, `quota`\n(`read_tenant_quota_state_locked`), and `events` (the rollup increment) all do. Under FORCE\neach still sees exactly the rows the app predicate already returns, so no legitimate query\nresult changes. (The 0002 backfill `INSERT…SELECT` ran as owner without the GUC, but that\ncompletes before 0004 enables FORCE, so it is unaffected.) The migration should ship with a\nfails-before/passes-after tenant-isolation test proving a query with the GUC unset returns\nzero rows — which is why this is routed to the remediation role (schema change + test)\nrather than patched inline by the security stage, consistent with how gating dependency\nbumps are routed (U-19/D2).\n\n**Related observation (out of change-set scope, not counted):** migration `0001` gives the\n`events` table the same latent gap (ENABLE without FORCE, owner = app role). The FORCE\nmigration should cover `events` too for consistency; flagged here for the remediation role's\nawareness though `events` is outside this feature's surface.\n\n## Fixes applied\n\nNone. The new endpoint code required no changes (clean). The single critical is a\nschema-migration remediation routed to the remediation/debugging role (see above), so\n`fixed_count = 0`.\n\n## Could not remediate — human/remediation review required\n\n- **Row 1 (RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`).** Requires a new alembic migration +\n  isolation test; routed to the remediation role. Exact verified-safe recipe above.\n\n## Action required\n\n- **OSV `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest → 9.0.3).** Below the CVSS 7.0 gate floor (6.8),\n  dev-only, and **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` with a review date\n  (`ignoreUntil = 2026-10-09`). No action this cycle; the major-version bump (pytest 8→9)\n  is tracked as a deliberate dev-dependency upgrade. Not introduced by this feature.\n\n## STRIDE mechanism verification (6d)\n\n8 named threats in `plan.md`; 7 mechanisms present-and-effective, 1 present-but-inert.\n\n| Threat | Mechanism | Evidence | Status |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Spoofing (auth) | `require_api_key` composed in `_require_authenticated_and_throttled` | `routes/usage_daily.py:23-30,36` | ✓ effective |\n| Tampering (`date` injection) | anchored `^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$` + `date.fromisoformat` + `[now-90d,now+1d]` → 400; value never reaches SQL as text (bound `:day_start/:day_end`) | `schemas/usage_daily.py:24,80-102`; `usage_repo.py:229-243` | ✓ effective |\n| Tampering (param smuggling) | `DailyUsageQueryParams(extra=\"forbid\")` | `schemas/usage_daily.py:44,46` | ✓ effective |\n| Repudiation | `logger.info(\"usage.daily.read\", …)` (no values, only counts) | `usage_daily_service.py:46-53` | ✓ effective |\n| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — primary | `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` first predicate, from principal; no object-id input | `usage_repo.py:236`; `routes/usage_daily.py` | ✓ effective |\n| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — backstop | `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS via `SET LOCAL` | migration `0002:67-73` | ✗ **inert (owner, no FORCE)** — row 1 |\n| Info Disclosure (error leak) | central `handle_unexpected_error` generic 500; service adds no try/except; `DailyUsageResponse(extra=\"forbid\")` | `api/errors.py:97-116`; `usage_daily_service.py`; `schemas/usage_daily.py:119-122` | ✓ effective |\n| DoS | Tier-2 `enforce_tier2_rate_limit` (redis token bucket, principal-keyed post-auth) + Tier-1 edge + date bound + single-day GROUP BY | `auth/rate_limit.py:136`; `routes/usage_daily.py:29` | ✓ effective |\n| EoP | `require_api_key` only, no admin gate needed, no object-id → no pivot | `routes/usage_daily.py:36` | ✓ effective |\n\nEfficacy answers (U-02): topology — Tier-2 runs **after** auth so it is principal-keyed not\nIP-keyed (✓); DB privilege — RLS owner check → **inert without FORCE** (✗, the critical);\nasync runtime — no CPU-hard/blocking sync calls in the async handlers (✓); contract drift —\nerror scrubber owns every error body, log facade strips control chars (✓).\n\n## STRIDE delta / attack-surface reconciliation (6f)\n\n`stride_new_threats: 0`. New surface introduced by the diff = the `GET /v1/usage/daily`\nroute, the `aggregate_daily_event_counts` read query, and the `usage.daily.read` log event.\nEvery one is covered by an existing `plan.md` threat-model entry (verified against\n`surface-delta.md`, which matched the diff). No new outbound calls, subprocess, SSRF sink,\nstored data, or privilege surface. No uncovered surface → no addendum entries. (The RLS\ninefficacy is an *efficacy* finding on an existing mitigation, 6d, not a new-surface gap.)\n\n## ast-grep (structural, advisory-only — not counted)\n\nRan the SQL/async structural checks (F-M4-5 trigger: diff touches SQL + async entrypoints).\nOne hit: `text(f\"…\")` at `usage_repo.py:134` — this is `count_usage_rollups`, a\n**pre-existing, byte-for-byte-unchanged** function (diff hunks are lines 1-5 and 198-248\nonly), already triaged with a `nosemgrep` pragma and a fixed-literal (non-client) WHERE\nclause. The **new** `aggregate_daily_event_counts` uses a plain bound-param `text(\"\"\"…\"\"\")`\nwith no interpolation — clean. No blocking-call/KDF-on-event-loop hits. Advisory only; feeds\nno count.\n\n## ASVS 5.0.0 (6g)\n\nTriggered chapters (from plan `## ASVS Compliance`): V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V11, V13, V16.\nL1/L2 verified universally; no new in-scope L3 (reused Argon2id path's 11.2.4 already met).\n\n- V1 (parameterized SQL): bound params, no interpolation of caller input — met.\n- V2 (validation + anti-automation): `parse_daily_date` allowlist + Tier-1/Tier-2 throttle — met.\n- V6 (auth): `require_api_key` reused — met.\n- V8 (8.2.2 object-level authz / tenant isolation): met **at the application layer** by the\n  `api_key_id`-first predicate + no object-id input. The RLS defense-in-depth backstop is\n  degraded (row 1) — surfaced once as the 6d critical, not double-counted here.\n- V11 (crypto): reused Argon2id key verification — met.\n- V13 (config / least-privilege): app role `NOBYPASSRLS` (infra) — met; the FORCE gap is the\n  6d finding.\n- V16 (logging & error handling): structured `usage.daily.read`, no PII/values/raw body;\n  fail-closed central error envelope — met.\n\n`asvs.reconciled: true` — no unmet/unwaived code/config L1/L2 or in-scope-L3 item (the ASVS\nobject-authz requirement is satisfied by the present primary control; the inert RLS backstop\nis captured as the 6d critical that already flips `status` to issues-found).\n\n## Input / data surface reconciliation\n\n- **input_surface** — 1 implemented source (`GET /v1/usage/daily?date=…`), with BOTH a\n  validation contract (`DailyUsageQueryParams` + `parse_daily_date`, acceptance AC3-6) AND a\n  rate-limit policy (Tier-2 principal-keyed + Tier-1, acceptance AC13). `uncontrolled: []`,\n  reconciled.\n- **data_surface** — pure read; the diff stores no new field/table/column/cache/blob.\n  `classified: 0`, `unprotected: []`, reconciled. (`data-protection-conventions` not\n  triggered — `usage_rollup` was classified non-sensitive operational metering data by the\n  prior feature.)\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":192,"cache_read_input_tokens":128697,"output_tokens":5936,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":192},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":5936,"cache_read_input_tokens":128697,"cache_creation_input_tokens":192,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":192,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccw1PQdavDi2D6ThivqSd","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"3bfea204-e0f0-4c73-8565-f8da52dec15c","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:50:14.827Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"3bfea204-e0f0-4c73-8565-f8da52dec15c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c93d3662-5462-4799-b6d7-cd0b2d4e2c75","agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NwCcuWyQiN2xB835uPQD9v","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-report.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"uuid":"89ce0328-ab6c-4ced-8376-46fe1b9b3466","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:50:14.954Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"update","filePath":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-report.md","content":"---\nstatus: issues-found\nran_at: 2026-07-11T21:30:09Z\nscope: diff\nsince_commit: 791a37c903a0420cfa81ec90e35cdbfe74dc9443\ncritical_count: 1\nwarning_count: 0\nfixed_count: 0\ntotal_findings: 2\nsemgrep_findings: 0\nosv_findings: 0\ncheckov_findings: null\ntrivy_findings: null\nstride_mechanisms_verified: 7\nstride_mechanisms_missing: 1\nstride_new_threats: 0\n---\n\n# Security report — `usage-daily` (`GET /v1/usage/daily`)\n\nScope: working-tree change set since `791a37c` (diff-scoping-conventions). Additive\ncustomer-scoped read endpoint. Files scanned:\n\n- NEW: `src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`, `src/services/usage_daily_service.py`,\n  `src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`, `tests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py`,\n  `tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py`\n- MODIFIED (additive): `src/main.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`\n\n## Bottom line\n\nThe new endpoint's own code is clean: SQL is fully parameterized/bound, the `date` input\nis validated by an anchored ReDoS-safe allowlist, the tenant predicate is `api_key_id`-first\nfrom the authenticated principal, errors fail closed, and no secrets/new dependencies were\nintroduced. **One blocking critical remains** — the RLS backstop the plan names as a\ndefense-in-depth control for the IDOR threat is **inert for the application role** (a\npre-existing migration-0002 gap). The primary app-level tenant predicate is present and\ncorrect, so the endpoint is **not independently exploitable** for cross-tenant reads, but\nper the presence-is-not-efficacy rule (U-02) a named-but-inert security mechanism is a\ncritical and is routed to remediation.\n\n## Tools run\n\n| Tool | Result | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Semgrep (native 1.169.0, `p/secrets` + `p/owasp-top-ten` + `p/python` + `p/default`, 1145 rules) | 0 findings | Scanned exactly the 5 change-set code files; clean. The Docker wrapper could not run — its container cannot resolve `semgrep.dev` (offline registry). Ran the **native** binary instead (host resolves fine). `.pipeline/semgrep.json`. |\n| OSV Scanner | 0 unfiltered (1 filtered/waived) | Scanned `poetry.lock` (80 pkgs). Only finding = `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest 8.3.4, CVSS 6.8 Medium, dev-only), **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` (below the 7.0 gate floor; not in the deployed surface). No new dependency introduced by this feature. `.pipeline/osv.json`. |\n| Gitleaks | 0 in change-set | 128 tree-wide hits, all in `.venv/` (vendored botocore data), `.pipeline/archive/`, `docs/`, and pre-existing test fixtures (`test_schemas_events.py`, `test_usage_export_endpoint.py`) — **none** in any change-set file. `.pipeline/gitleaks.json`. |\n| lockfile-check (supply-chain) | clean | No manifest/lockfile drift; no unpinned specifiers. |\n| asvs-sast (Tier-1) | 0 critical, 0 warning | No JWT-none / fast-hash / non-CSPRNG / weak-cipher in the diff. |\n| ast-grep (structural, advisory-only) | 1 hit, pre-existing | See \"ast-grep\" below. |\n| Trivy fs / config | skipped (disclosed) | Docker DNS unreachable (`mirror.gcr.io`) — vuln DB pull failed. Not a required scanner (no Dockerfile in change-set); OSV covered SCA. |\n| Checkov | not run (n/a) | No `infra/` change in the change-set. |\n\n## Complete findings inventory\n\n| # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | manual-6d | STRIDE-efficacy: `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS backstop inert for app role (owner, no FORCE) | critical (per U-02) | no (primary app predicate present; no object-id input) | `alembic/versions/0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py:67-73` (+ runtime owner in `src/db/session.py`) | could-not-remediate |\n| 2 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g (PYSEC-2026-1845, pytest 8.3.4) | medium (CVSS 6.8) | no (dev-only, not in prod container) | `poetry.lock` | reported-only (waived, `osv-scanner.toml`) |\n\n`total_findings = 2`. Semgrep, gitleaks (in-scope), lockfile-check, asvs-sast, and manual\nchecks 6a/6c/6e/6f/6g each produced **0** findings, so contribute no rows.\n\n## Critical finding detail (row 1)\n\n**STRIDE mitigation ineffective — RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`.**\n\nThe plan's Information-Disclosure (IDOR) mitigation claims: *\"plus RLS policy\n`usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` (migration 0002) **enforced** via `SET LOCAL\napp.current_api_key_id`.\"* That claim is false for the application role:\n\n- Migration `0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py` runs `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup ENABLE\n  ROW LEVEL SECURITY` and `CREATE POLICY usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` but **does not**\n  run `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`.\n- Migrations execute as `meterly_app` (per `0003`'s own comment: the migration job resolves\n  the DB URL through the same secrets facade the app uses → the `meterly_app` credential),\n  so `meterly_app` **owns** `usage_rollup`. The runtime app also connects as `meterly_app`.\n- In PostgreSQL, a **table owner bypasses non-FORCE RLS** regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS`. So\n  the policy is inert for the app role — the backstop does not fire.\n- This is confirmed by the codebase's own intent: migration `0003` applies `ALTER TABLE\n  quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` with a comment documenting exactly this owner-bypass\n  semantics. `0001` (events) and `0002` (usage_rollup) omit it — an inconsistency/oversight,\n  not a deliberate exception.\n\n**Why it is not independently exploitable through this feature:** the primary tenant control\nis present and correct — `aggregate_daily_event_counts` (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`)\nuses `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` as its **first** predicate, bound from\n`principal.api_key_id` (never client input), and the endpoint accepts **no** `customer_id` /\n`api_key_id` parameter (`extra=\"forbid\"`), so there is no IDOR selector. Cross-tenant reads\nare blocked at the application layer today. The finding is that the *defense-in-depth\nbackstop* — the layer meant to catch a future missing-predicate bug — is silently disabled.\n\n**Verified-safe remediation (for the remediation/debugging role):** add a new forward\nmigration `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`:\n- upgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`\n- downgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup NO FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`\n- `down_revision` chained to `0003`.\n\nThis is **behavior-preserving**: I verified that **every runtime reader/writer of\n`usage_rollup` executes inside `scoped_transaction`** (which sets `app.current_api_key_id`\nvia `SET LOCAL`) — the four services `usage_daily`, `usage_export`, `quota`\n(`read_tenant_quota_state_locked`), and `events` (the rollup increment) all do. Under FORCE\neach still sees exactly the rows the app predicate already returns, so no legitimate query\nresult changes. (The 0002 backfill `INSERT…SELECT` ran as owner without the GUC, but that\ncompletes before 0004 enables FORCE, so it is unaffected.) The migration should ship with a\nfails-before/passes-after tenant-isolation test proving a query with the GUC unset returns\nzero rows — which is why this is routed to the remediation role (schema change + test)\nrather than patched inline by the security stage, consistent with how gating dependency\nbumps are routed (U-19/D2).\n\n**Related observation (out of change-set scope, not counted):** migration `0001` gives the\n`events` table the same latent gap (ENABLE without FORCE, owner = app role). The FORCE\nmigration should cover `events` too for consistency; flagged here for the remediation role's\nawareness though `events` is outside this feature's surface.\n\n## Fixes applied\n\nNone. The new endpoint code required no changes (clean). The single critical is a\nschema-migration remediation routed to the remediation/debugging role (see above), so\n`fixed_count = 0`.\n\n## Could not remediate — human/remediation review required\n\n- **Row 1 (RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`).** Requires a new alembic migration +\n  isolation test; routed to the remediation role. Exact verified-safe recipe above.\n\n## Action required\n\n- **OSV `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest → 9.0.3).** Below the CVSS 7.0 gate floor (6.8),\n  dev-only, and **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` with a review date\n  (`ignoreUntil = 2026-10-09`). No action this cycle; the major-version bump (pytest 8→9)\n  is tracked as a deliberate dev-dependency upgrade. Not introduced by this feature.\n\n## STRIDE mechanism verification (6d)\n\n8 named threats in `plan.md`; 7 mechanisms present-and-effective, 1 present-but-inert.\n\n| Threat | Mechanism | Evidence | Status |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Spoofing (auth) | `require_api_key` composed in `_require_authenticated_and_throttled` | `routes/usage_daily.py:23-30,36` | ✓ effective |\n| Tampering (`date` injection) | anchored `^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$` + `date.fromisoformat` + `[now-90d,now+1d]` → 400; value never reaches SQL as text (bound `:day_start/:day_end`) | `schemas/usage_daily.py:24,80-102`; `usage_repo.py:229-243` | ✓ effective |\n| Tampering (param smuggling) | `DailyUsageQueryParams(extra=\"forbid\")` | `schemas/usage_daily.py:44,46` | ✓ effective |\n| Repudiation | `logger.info(\"usage.daily.read\", …)` (no values, only counts) | `usage_daily_service.py:46-53` | ✓ effective |\n| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — primary | `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` first predicate, from principal; no object-id input | `usage_repo.py:236`; `routes/usage_daily.py` | ✓ effective |\n| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — backstop | `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS via `SET LOCAL` | migration `0002:67-73` | ✗ **inert (owner, no FORCE)** — row 1 |\n| Info Disclosure (error leak) | central `handle_unexpected_error` generic 500; service adds no try/except; `DailyUsageResponse(extra=\"forbid\")` | `api/errors.py:97-116`; `usage_daily_service.py`; `schemas/usage_daily.py:119-122` | ✓ effective |\n| DoS | Tier-2 `enforce_tier2_rate_limit` (redis token bucket, principal-keyed post-auth) + Tier-1 edge + date bound + single-day GROUP BY | `auth/rate_limit.py:136`; `routes/usage_daily.py:29` | ✓ effective |\n| EoP | `require_api_key` only, no admin gate needed, no object-id → no pivot | `routes/usage_daily.py:36` | ✓ effective |\n\nEfficacy answers (U-02): topology — Tier-2 runs **after** auth so it is principal-keyed not\nIP-keyed (✓); DB privilege — RLS owner check → **inert without FORCE** (✗, the critical);\nasync runtime — no CPU-hard/blocking sync calls in the async handlers (✓); contract drift —\nerror scrubber owns every error body, log facade strips control chars (✓).\n\n## STRIDE delta / attack-surface reconciliation (6f)\n\n`stride_new_threats: 0`. New surface introduced by the diff = the `GET /v1/usage/daily`\nroute, the `aggregate_daily_event_counts` read query, and the `usage.daily.read` log event.\nEvery one is covered by an existing `plan.md` threat-model entry (verified against\n`surface-delta.md`, which matched the diff). No new outbound calls, subprocess, SSRF sink,\nstored data, or privilege surface. No uncovered surface → no addendum entries. (The RLS\ninefficacy is an *efficacy* finding on an existing mitigation, 6d, not a new-surface gap.)\n\n## ast-grep (structural, advisory-only — not counted)\n\nRan the SQL/async structural checks (F-M4-5 trigger: diff touches SQL + async entrypoints).\nOne hit: `text(f\"…\")` at `usage_repo.py:134` — this is `count_usage_rollups`, a\n**pre-existing, byte-for-byte-unchanged** function (diff hunks are lines 1-5 and 198-248\nonly), already triaged with a `nosemgrep` pragma and a fixed-literal (non-client) WHERE\nclause. The **new** `aggregate_daily_event_counts` uses a plain bound-param `text(\"\"\"…\"\"\")`\nwith no interpolation — clean. No blocking-call/KDF-on-event-loop hits. Advisory only; feeds\nno count.\n\n## ASVS 5.0.0 (6g)\n\nTriggered chapters (from plan `## ASVS Compliance`): V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V11, V13, V16.\nL1/L2 verified universally; no new in-scope L3 (reused Argon2id path's 11.2.4 already met).\n\n- V1 (parameterized SQL): bound params, no interpolation of caller input — met.\n- V2 (validation + anti-automation): `parse_daily_date` allowlist + Tier-1/Tier-2 throttle — met.\n- V6 (auth): `require_api_key` reused — met.\n- V8 (8.2.2 object-level authz / tenant isolation): met **at the application layer** by the\n  `api_key_id`-first predicate + no object-id input. The RLS defense-in-depth backstop is\n  degraded (row 1) — surfaced once as the 6d critical, not double-counted here.\n- V11 (crypto): reused Argon2id key verification — met.\n- V13 (config / least-privilege): app role `NOBYPASSRLS` (infra) — met; the FORCE gap is the\n  6d finding.\n- V16 (logging & error handling): structured `usage.daily.read`, no PII/values/raw body;\n  fail-closed central error envelope — met.\n\n`asvs.reconciled: true` — no unmet/unwaived code/config L1/L2 or in-scope-L3 item (the ASVS\nobject-authz requirement is satisfied by the present primary control; the inert RLS backstop\nis captured as the 6d critical that already flips `status` to issues-found).\n\n## Input / data surface reconciliation\n\n- **input_surface** — 1 implemented source (`GET /v1/usage/daily?date=…`), with BOTH a\n  validation contract (`DailyUsageQueryParams` + `parse_daily_date`, acceptance AC3-6) AND a\n  rate-limit policy (Tier-2 principal-keyed + Tier-1, acceptance AC13). `uncontrolled: []`,\n  reconciled.\n- **data_surface** — pure read; the diff stores no new field/table/column/cache/blob.\n  `classified: 0`, `unprotected: []`, reconciled. (`data-protection-conventions` not\n  triggered — `usage_rollup` was classified non-sensitive operational metering data by the\n  prior feature.)\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":198,"newStart":1,"newLines":204,"lines":[" ---","-status: clean","-ran_at: 2026-07-10T01:55:58Z","+status: issues-found","+ran_at: 2026-07-11T21:30:09Z"," scope: diff","-since_commit: ef3fb3f686649d0ee0d37707dd61013b5e1d28f4","-critical_count: 0","-warning_count: 2","-fixed_count: 1","-total_findings: 3","+since_commit: 791a37c903a0420cfa81ec90e35cdbfe74dc9443","+critical_count: 1","+warning_count: 0","+fixed_count: 0","+total_findings: 2"," semgrep_findings: 0","-osv_findings: 2","-checkov_findings: 0","-trivy_findings: 0","-stride_mechanisms_verified: 10","-stride_mechanisms_missing: 0","+osv_findings: 0","+checkov_findings: null","+trivy_findings: null","+stride_mechanisms_verified: 7","+stride_mechanisms_missing: 1"," stride_new_threats: 0","-asvs_reconciled: true"," ---"," ","-# Security report — quota administration (GET /v1/quotas list + DELETE /v1/quotas)","+# Security report — `usage-daily` (`GET /v1/usage/daily`)"," ","-Branch `feature/quota-admin`. Scope = diff against `HEAD` (ef3fb3f). **No critical findings.**","-The implementation is well-hardened: parameterized SQL, anchored allowlist validation, admin-scope","-gate, per-tenant `api_key_id` filtering with FORCE RLS backstop, minimal response projection, and a","-fail-closed generic-500 error boundary.","+Scope: working-tree change set since `791a37c` (diff-scoping-conventions). Additive","+customer-scoped read endpoint. Files scanned:"," ","-## Tools run this pass","+- NEW: `src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`, `src/services/usage_daily_service.py`,","+  `src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`, `tests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py`,","+  `tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py`","+- MODIFIED (additive): `src/main.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`"," ","-| Tool | Scope | Result |","-|---|---|---|","-| Semgrep (auto + p/secrets + p/owasp-top-ten + p/python) | 7 changed code/test files | 0 findings, 0 errors |","-| Gitleaks (dir) | full tree | 0 in change set (128 out-of-scope, see below) |","-| OSV Scanner | poetry.lock | 1 CVE (2 alias ids), dev-only, below gate floor |","-| Trivy fs (vuln,secret,misconfig) | src/ | 0 findings |","-| lockfile-check | change set | clean (no manifest/lockfile drift) |","-| asvs-sast (Tier-1 deterministic) | change set | 0 critical |","-| ast-grep (structural, advisory) | changed src | clean (see 6d) |","-| generate-sbom | project | wrote .pipeline/sbom.cdx.json, 65 components |","+## Bottom line"," ","-Checkov not run: **no `infra/` `.tf` file changed** in this diff (the only untracked `infra/` entries","-were the local `.terraform/` provider cache — see fix below). Trivy `config`/`image` not run: no","-Dockerfile or built image in the change set. Both legitimately omitted from `scan_artifacts`.","+The new endpoint's own code is clean: SQL is fully parameterized/bound, the `date` input","+is validated by an anchored ReDoS-safe allowlist, the tenant predicate is `api_key_id`-first","+from the authenticated principal, errors fail closed, and no secrets/new dependencies were","+introduced. **One blocking critical remains** — the RLS backstop the plan names as a","+defense-in-depth control for the IDOR threat is **inert for the application role** (a","+pre-existing migration-0002 gap). The primary app-level tenant predicate is present and","+correct, so the endpoint is **not independently exploitable** for cross-tenant reads, but","+per the presence-is-not-efficacy rule (U-02) a named-but-inert security mechanism is a","+critical and is routed to remediation."," ","-## Change-set diff-scope","+## Tools run"," ","-Tracked: `PROJECT.md`, `.gitignore` (fixed this pass), `src/api/middleware.py`,","-`src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`,","-`src/services/quota_service.py`, `tests/test_schemas_quotas.py`. Untracked:","-`tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py`, `infra/.terraform.lock.hcl` (the provider lock —","-legitimately committable, kept).","+| Tool | Result | Notes |","+|---|---|---|","+| Semgrep (native 1.169.0, `p/secrets` + `p/owasp-top-ten` + `p/python` + `p/default`, 1145 rules) | 0 findings | Scanned exactly the 5 change-set code files; clean. The Docker wrapper could not run — its container cannot resolve `semgrep.dev` (offline registry). Ran the **native** binary instead (host resolves fine). `.pipeline/semgrep.json`. |","+| OSV Scanner | 0 unfiltered (1 filtered/waived) | Scanned `poetry.lock` (80 pkgs). Only finding = `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest 8.3.4, CVSS 6.8 Medium, dev-only), **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` (below the 7.0 gate floor; not in the deployed surface). No new dependency introduced by this feature. `.pipeline/osv.json`. |","+| Gitleaks | 0 in change-set | 128 tree-wide hits, all in `.venv/` (vendored botocore data), `.pipeline/archive/`, `docs/`, and pre-existing test fixtures (`test_schemas_events.py`, `test_usage_export_endpoint.py`) — **none** in any change-set file. `.pipeline/gitleaks.json`. |","+| lockfile-check (supply-chain) | clean | No manifest/lockfile drift; no unpinned specifiers. |","+| asvs-sast (Tier-1) | 0 critical, 0 warning | No JWT-none / fast-hash / non-CSPRNG / weak-cipher in the diff. |","+| ast-grep (structural, advisory-only) | 1 hit, pre-existing | See \"ast-grep\" below. |","+| Trivy fs / config | skipped (disclosed) | Docker DNS unreachable (`mirror.gcr.io`) — vuln DB pull failed. Not a required scanner (no Dockerfile in change-set); OSV covered SCA. |","+| Checkov | not run (n/a) | No `infra/` change in the change-set. |"," "," ## Complete findings inventory"," "," | # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |"," |---|---|---|---|---|---|---|","-| 1 | osv | CVE-2025-71176 (PYSEC-2026-1845 / GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g) | Medium (CVSS ~6.8) | no | poetry.lock — pytest 8.3.4 | action-required |","-| 2 | manual-6a | terraform-provider-binaries-not-gitignored | Low | no | .gitignore / infra/.terraform/ | fixed |","-| 3 | manual-6d | tier1-throttle-ip-keying-behind-alb (efficacy, pre-existing, out of diff-scope) | Low | no | src/api/middleware.py:118 | reported-only |","+| 1 | manual-6d | STRIDE-efficacy: `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS backstop inert for app role (owner, no FORCE) | critical (per U-02) | no (primary app predicate present; no object-id input) | `alembic/versions/0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py:67-73` (+ runtime owner in `src/db/session.py`) | could-not-remediate |","+| 2 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g (PYSEC-2026-1845, pytest 8.3.4) | medium (CVSS 6.8) | no (dev-only, not in prod container) | `poetry.lock` | reported-only (waived, `osv-scanner.toml`) |"," ","-`total_findings: 3`. `osv_findings: 2` in the status JSON is the reconcile convention (unique alias","-id count) for the single logical pytest CVE (row 1).","+`total_findings = 2`. Semgrep, gitleaks (in-scope), lockfile-check, asvs-sast, and manual","+checks 6a/6c/6e/6f/6g each produced **0** findings, so contribute no rows."," ","-## Fixes applied","+## Critical finding detail (row 1)"," ","-**[fixed] Row 2 — Terraform provider binaries were not gitignored.** `.gitignore` lacked a","-`.terraform/` entry, so `git ls-files --others` pulled ~108 MB of vendored HashiCorp provider","-executables (`terraform-provider-aws_v5.100.0_x5.exe`, null, random) plus the module cache into the","-diff-scoped change set — a repo-hygiene / minor supply-chain surface (large signed third-party","-binaries entering the tree the pipeline hashes and would commit).","-- **Before:** `.gitignore` lines 17–18 = `*.tfstate` / `*.tfvars` only.","-- **After:** added `.terraform/` (line 19). Verified `git check-ignore` now excludes the provider","-  `.exe`s; the change set drops from 8 untracked entries to 2 (test file + `.terraform.lock.hcl`).","-- The provider **lock** `infra/.terraform.lock.hcl` is deliberately **not** ignored (pinning provider","-  versions/hashes is good supply-chain practice) — it stays committable.","+**STRIDE mitigation ineffective — RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`.**"," ","-## Action required (report-only, not auto-fixed)","+The plan's Information-Disclosure (IDOR) mitigation claims: *\"plus RLS policy","+`usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` (migration 0002) **enforced** via `SET LOCAL","+app.current_api_key_id`.\"* That claim is false for the application role:"," ","-**Row 1 — pytest 8.3.4 has a vulnerable tmpdir-handling CVE (CVE-2025-71176).**","-- Package: `pytest 8.3.4` (PyPI), a **dev/test-only** dependency (not on the request path, not in the","-  runtime container).","-- CVSS 3.1: `AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:L` ≈ **6.8 (Medium)** — **below** the deploy gate's","-  ≥7.0 High/Critical floor, so it does **not** block. `osv_max_cvss: 6.8`, `osv_waiver: null`.","-- **Safe version: upgrade `pytest` to `>= 9.0.3`.** Per policy, dependency manifests/lockfiles are not","-  modified here; a maintainer bumps `pyproject.toml`/`poetry.lock`. Not routed to debugging (below the","-  ≥7.0 gate floor); the human decides.","+- Migration `0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py` runs `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup ENABLE","+  ROW LEVEL SECURITY` and `CREATE POLICY usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` but **does not**","+  run `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`.","+- Migrations execute as `meterly_app` (per `0003`'s own comment: the migration job resolves","+  the DB URL through the same secrets facade the app uses → the `meterly_app` credential),","+  so `meterly_app` **owns** `usage_rollup`. The runtime app also connects as `meterly_app`.","+- In PostgreSQL, a **table owner bypasses non-FORCE RLS** regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS`. So","+  the policy is inert for the app role — the backstop does not fire.","+- This is confirmed by the codebase's own intent: migration `0003` applies `ALTER TABLE","+  quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` with a comment documenting exactly this owner-bypass","+  semantics. `0001` (events) and `0002` (usage_rollup) omit it — an inconsistency/oversight,","+  not a deliberate exception."," ","-## Could not remediate","+**Why it is not independently exploitable through this feature:** the primary tenant control","+is present and correct — `aggregate_daily_event_counts` (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`)","+uses `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` as its **first** predicate, bound from","+`principal.api_key_id` (never client input), and the endpoint accepts **no** `customer_id` /","+`api_key_id` parameter (`extra=\"forbid\"`), so there is no IDOR selector. Cross-tenant reads","+are blocked at the application layer today. The finding is that the *defense-in-depth","+backstop* — the layer meant to catch a future missing-predicate bug — is silently disabled."," ","-None. No finding required a design decision or escalation.","+**Verified-safe remediation (for the remediation/debugging role):** add a new forward","+migration `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`:","+- upgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`","+- downgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup NO FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`","+- `down_revision` chained to `0003`."," ","-## Manual security checks (steps 6a–6g)","+This is **behavior-preserving**: I verified that **every runtime reader/writer of","+`usage_rollup` executes inside `scoped_transaction`** (which sets `app.current_api_key_id`","+via `SET LOCAL`) — the four services `usage_daily`, `usage_export`, `quota`","+(`read_tenant_quota_state_locked`), and `events` (the rollup increment) all do. Under FORCE","+each still sees exactly the rows the app predicate already returns, so no legitimate query","+result changes. (The 0002 backfill `INSERT…SELECT` ran as owner without the GUC, but that","+completes before 0004 enables FORCE, so it is unaffected.) The migration should ship with a","+fails-before/passes-after tenant-isolation test proving a query with the GUC unset returns","+zero rows — which is why this is routed to the remediation role (schema change + test)","+rather than patched inline by the security stage, consistent with how gating dependency","+bumps are routed (U-19/D2)."," ","-**6a — Secrets / API-key exposure:** clean. No hardcoded credential literal in any changed file","-(grep + Semgrep p/secrets + Gitleaks all clean on the change set). `.env` is gitignored and untracked;","-`PROJECT.md` diff is only the feature description; no secret in config. The server sets `api_key_id`","-from the authenticated principal and never accepts a client-supplied `scope`/`api_key_id`","-(`extra='forbid'` on both request schemas — mass-assignment defense).","+**Related observation (out of change-set scope, not counted):** migration `0001` gives the","+`events` table the same latent gap (ENABLE without FORCE, owner = app role). The FORCE","+migration should cover `events` too for consistency; flagged here for the remediation role's","+awareness though `events` is outside this feature's surface."," ","-**6b — Row-level security:** clean. Every `quotas` query is scoped by `api_key_id` first —","-`list_quotas` (`WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id`), `delete_quota`","-(`WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = … AND metric = …`), `upsert_quota`","-(`ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`). Backstop verified: migration `0003` sets","-`ALTER TABLE quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` + policy `quotas_tenant_isolation`, and","-`scoped_transaction` sets `app.current_api_key_id` via `SET LOCAL set_config(...)`","-(`src/db/session.py:58-85`). Efficacy-correct (U-02): the app role owns the table, so FORCE is","-required and present — a non-FORCE policy would be inert.","+## Fixes applied"," ","-**6c — Input / output sanitization:** clean.","-- DELETE query params validated by `QuotaDeleteParams` (anchored `constr` allowlists","-  `^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,128/64}$`, ReDoS-safe, `extra='forbid'`) before the handler — an injection","-  payload (`' OR 1=1--`) is rejected at the boundary (422), never reaching the sink (AC9).","-- GET accepts no body/query/path parameter — no injectable input.","-- All new SQL uses SQLAlchemy `text()` with bound parameters only — no string interpolation. ast-grep","-  structural check for `session.execute(text(f\"…\"))` in the repo: **0 hits** (confirms AC15).","-- Output: `response_model=list[QuotaResponse]` projects only `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}`","-  (no `api_key_id`/timestamps). JSON API, no HTML/JS/URL sink — no output-encoding exposure.","+None. The new endpoint code required no changes (clean). The single critical is a","+schema-migration remediation routed to the remediation/debugging role (see above), so","+`fixed_count = 0`."," ","-**6d — STRIDE mechanism verification (10/10 present + efficacy-correct, 0 missing):**","-1. Spoofing → `_require_admin_and_throttled` = `require_api_key` (Argon2id) + `scope=='admin'`→403 — `routes/quotas.py:35-52`. ✓","-2. Tampering/SQLi → anchored `constr` + parameterized `text()` — `schemas/quotas.py:15-16`, `quotas_repo.py:205-214`. ✓","-3. Tampering/mass-assignment → `ConfigDict(extra='forbid')`, server-set `api_key_id` — `schemas/quotas.py:60`. ✓","-4. Repudiation → `quota.delete` INFO (userId, action, customer_id[redacted], metric, requestId) — `quota_service.py:116-122`. ✓","-5. Info-disclosure (GET) → minimal `response_model` + `api_key_id`-scoped SELECT + FORCE RLS — `routes/quotas.py:68`, `quotas_repo.py:161-187`. ✓","-6. Info-disclosure (safe-error) → `handle_unexpected_error` returns generic `{code:internal}` 500, detail logged server-side only; `scoped_transaction` rolls back (fail-closed, no partial DELETE) — `errors.py:97-118`, `db/session.py:65`. ✓ (AC19)","-7. DoS (flood) → Tier-1 IP throttle + Tier-2 per-`api_key_id` bucket — `middleware.py`, `rate_limit.py:136-154`. ✓ (efficacy: see below)","-8. EoP (function-level) → `scope=='admin'`→403, `quota.forbidden` logged — `routes/quotas.py:44-51`. ✓","-9. EoP (IDOR/BOLA) → `api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS → cross-tenant DELETE matches 0 rows → 404 — `quotas_repo.py`, `db/session.py`, `0003`. ✓","-10. Tampering (`usage_rollup` integrity) → `delete_quota` issues **only** a DELETE on `quotas`, never touches `usage_rollup` — `quotas_repo.py:205-214`. ✓","+## Could not remediate — human/remediation review required"," ","-Efficacy questions (U-02) answered:","-- **Async runtime:** no CPU-hard KDF or blocking sync SDK call on the event loop in the changed handlers.","-  ast-grep for `argon2.*`/`bcrypt.*` in the changed src: **0 hits**; the one `boto3.client` in the tree","-  is `src/config/secrets.py` (pre-existing, startup-time, not in this change set). All handler DB I/O","-  goes through the async session. ✓","-- **DB privilege:** FORCE RLS present + app-role owns the table (verified above). ✓","-- **Contract drift:** the safe-error scrubber (`handle_unexpected_error`) is a global catch-all that","-  covers the two new DB-I/O paths (AC19); response body carries no stack/SQL/type/path. ✓","-- **Topology (the one efficacy warning, row 3):** the Tier-1 pre-auth throttle keys its bucket on","-  `request.client.host` (`middleware.py:118`) and no `--proxy-headers`/`forwarded-allow-ips` trust is","-  configured, so **behind the ALB** Tier-1 would bucket per-ALB-node rather than per-real-client. This","-  is **pre-existing** middleware **not introduced by this diff** (the only middleware change here is","-  adding `\"DELETE\"` to CORS `allow_methods`), and for these admin routes the **effective** anti-abuse","-  control is **Tier-2**, which keys on `str(principal.api_key_id)` (`rate_limit.py:153`) — topology-","-  independent and proven per-principal by AC12. The LB readiness path `/heal