{"parentUuid":"982aa19a-a8cc-4f79-8805-35449f214a1d","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c93d3662-5462-4799-b6d7-cd0b2d4e2c75","agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013xEFFhXZ5a3nAJfNR8NzDw","type":"tool_result","content":"=== secrets in config/PROJECT.md diff ===\nwarning: in the working copy of '.claude/settings.json', CRLF will be replaced by LF the next time Git touches it\nno secret literals in tracked config diff\n=== settings.local.json (untracked) secrets ===\nno secret literals in settings.local.json\n=== confirm .env not tracked, .env in gitignore ===\n.env gitignored","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"8544299d-41ca-4fa2-92bb-f625bad1f509","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:52:04.257Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"=== secrets in config/PROJECT.md diff ===\nwarning: in the working copy of '.claude/settings.json', CRLF will be replaced by LF the next time Git touches it\nno secret literals in tracked config diff\n=== settings.local.json (untracked) secrets ===\nno secret literals in settings.local.json\n=== confirm .env not tracked, .env in gitignore ===\n.env gitignored","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"982aa19a-a8cc-4f79-8805-35449f214a1d","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"8544299d-41ca-4fa2-92bb-f625bad1f509","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a15312ba4ecaf116c","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccw1cD9PVUSmE3CMny4Qf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All checks pass. Both artifacts are written and the reconcile hook confirms `scan_reconciled: true` with no count mismatches or scope gaps.\n\n## Summary\n\nRan the security stage for `usage-daily` (diff-scoped to the working-tree change set since `791a37c`). Tools: **Semgrep** (native 1.169.0, p/secrets+p/owasp-top-ten+p/python+p/default, 1145 rules, all 7 change-set code files), **OSV**, **gitleaks**, **lockfile-check**, **asvs-sast**, **ast-grep** (SQL+async structural, advisory), plus manual STRIDE/ASVS/input-surface/data-surface reconciliation. Trivy-fs and the Semgrep Docker wrapper both hit a container-DNS wall (offline registry / `mirror.gcr.io`) — disclosed; Semgrep was run via the native binary instead, and OSV (native, no Docker) covered SCA.\n\n**Result: `status: issues-found`, 1 critical, 0 warnings, 0 fixed, 2 total findings.**\n\nThe new endpoint code is genuinely clean — parameterized/bound SQL, anchored ReDoS-safe `date` allowlist, `api_key_id`-first tenant predicate from the principal, no object-id input, fail-closed errors, no secrets, no new dependencies. The two findings:\n\n1. **CRITICAL (blocking) — inert RLS backstop.** The plan names `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS as an \"enforced\" defense-in-depth control for the IDOR threat, but migration `0002` sets `ENABLE` without `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`, and the app connects as the table owner (`meterly_app`) — so a PostgreSQL owner bypasses non-FORCE RLS and the backstop is inert. Confirmed by migration `0003`'s own comment, which applies `FORCE` to `quotas` for exactly this reason (`0001`/`0002` omit it). Not independently exploitable through this feature (the primary app-level predicate is present and there is no IDOR selector), but per the presence-is-not-efficacy rule (U-02) a named-but-inert mechanism is a critical. Routed to remediation as **could-not-remediate** with a verified-safe recipe (new migration `0004` adding `FORCE`, behavior-preserving because all four runtime `usage_rollup` readers/writers run inside `scoped_transaction`; ship with a fails-before/passes-after isolation test). `events` (0001) shares the latent gap — flagged for awareness.\n\n2. **Reported-only — OSV `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g`** (pytest 8.3.4, CVSS 6.8, dev-only), below the 7.0 gate floor and waived in the committed `osv-scanner.toml`. Not introduced by this feature.\n\nAll deterministic conjuncts read clean/true (`scan_reconciled: true`, `asvs.reconciled: true`, `osv_max_cvss: 0`, `input_surface.uncontrolled: []`, `data_surface.unprotected: []`); the loop-exit gate blocks solely on the honest `critical_count: 1`. I did not force the gate green — the parent's request to make it read true is conditional on a genuinely clean state, and one real critical remains.\n\nArtifacts written:\n- `/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-report.md`\n- `/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-status.json`\n\nRaw scanner output in `.pipeline/semgrep.json`, `.pipeline/osv.json`, `.pipeline/gitleaks.json`; reconciliation in `.pipeline/scan-reconciliation.json`."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1502,"cache_read_input_tokens":141062,"output_tokens":1327,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1502},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1327,"cache_read_input_tokens":141062,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1502,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1502,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccw1cBXA9kcbK1fVqiQhV","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"2b9a26fb-f1fc-4538-80d2-ffe0dd9656f8","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:52:24.542Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
